169
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:17,500
But he's gonna let me keep my box of human hair.
但他肯让我留下我那盒头发！

170
00:11:18,770 --> 00:11:24,140
So you gotta pick your battles. But the good news is, Gladys is yours.
所以我只能妥协了。 但好消息是，格拉达斯已经属于你了！

171
00:11:25,910 --> 00:11:28,400
Wow, what's the bad news?
哇，那坏消息呢！？

172
00:11:28,780 --> 00:11:32,050
- Who's Gladys? - Oh, she's that work of art I made.
-谁是格拉达斯？ -噢！她是我的手工作品，你见过啦

173
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:34,950
You know, with the woman coming out of the frame.
就是有个女人从画里面走出来的那幅画啊

174
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:39,590
And Monica gets to keep her?
噢，莫尼卡把她收下了吗？

175
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:42,960
In her house? I am so jealous.
放在这个房间里？我要嫉妒了！

176
00:11:44,970 --> 00:11:46,930
I didn't know you wanted her too.
噢！我不知道你也想要她啊！

177
00:11:49,070 --> 00:11:52,510
Well, I mean, sure, of course.
我..当然想要啊。

178
00:11:53,010 --> 00:11:55,170
But you already gave that to Monica, so..
但..你已经给了莫尼卡了，所以...

179
00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:59,140
- You know, I would give her up for you. - No, I couldn't let you do that.
-为了你，我可以放弃她。 -不行，我不可以让你这样做的。

180
00:11:59,310 --> 00:12:01,650
- No, but I want to. - But I don't want you to.
-但我想这样做。 -但我不想你这样做。

181
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:05,750
- But I insist. - But I insist harder.
-但我坚持！ -但我更坚持！

182
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,850
Girls. Girls. Stop. Okay, we'll flip a coin.
女生们！停一停好吗？我们投硬币决定吧。

183
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:13,220
Heads, she's Rachel's. Tails, she's Monica's.
正面，她是瑞秋的 反面，她就是莫尼卡的。

184
00:12:15,660 --> 00:12:19,500
- Tails. Monica, she's yours. - No, that landed in your food.
-反面！莫尼卡，她是你的了！ -不行，它掉到你的食物里了

185
00:12:20,530 --> 00:12:24,630
No, no, that's okay. You won fair and square. I'm so sad.
不，没关系，该赢的就该赢。我太难过了。

186
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:31,140
Then the little red squirrel took all of his acorns..
然后红色的小松鼠把他所有的橡子(果实)

187
00:12:31,310 --> 00:12:35,310
and put them in his little satchel and set off for..
放进他的小背包里, 离开了

188
00:12:36,350 --> 00:12:39,380
Okay. Someone's getting a little fussy. I think it's time for bed.
好啦!有人开始烦啦 我看该睡觉了

189
00:12:40,490 --> 00:12:42,420
Where's the little red squirrel going?
小松鼠去哪了?

190
00:12:47,230 --> 00:12:48,920
Hey, Joe?
嘿 乔伊！

191
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:55,660
Oh, that's so sweet.
哦，太好了

192
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:58,900
- What's up? - Bad news.
-什么事？ -坏消息

193
00:12:59,070 --> 00:13:03,910
I watched the tape and passed it along to my bosses and they weren't interested.
我看过了带子并把它交给我的老板们 但他们不感兴趣。

194
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:07,740
I'm sorry, man.
对不起，老兄。

195
00:13:08,950 --> 00:13:13,110
- But you watched the tape? - Yeah, I liked it.
-但...你看过这带子吗？ -是啊，我...我很喜欢啊！

196
00:13:14,290 --> 00:13:20,060
But my bosses didn't go for it. Stupid sons of bitches.
但...我的老板不喜欢。真他妈的可恶！

197
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:28,990
- You didn't watch the tape. - What? Of course I did.
-你没有看过这带子。 -什么！？我当然看啦！

198
00:13:29,170 --> 00:13:32,000
Look, it's one thing not to cast me, but to lie to me?
你不推荐我是一回事，但你对我说谎？

199
00:13:32,170 --> 00:13:35,300
- I'm not lying to you. I watched it. - You lied again.
-我没有说谎啊，我看了啦！ -你看，又说谎！

200
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:38,600
- I watched it. - Keep going, Pinocchio.
-我看了！ -继续说谎吧，匹诺曹！

201
00:13:39,810 --> 00:13:41,680
- I did. - No, you didn't.
-我看了！ -没有！ 你没看！

202
00:13:41,850 --> 00:13:43,910
I'm telling you, I watched the tape.
我告诉你，我看了这带子。

203
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:48,620
- Did you watch the tape? - No.
-你看过这带子吗？ -没有

204
00:13:53,190 --> 00:13:56,960
Hi. Look, I realize only one of us can get this grant.
嗨, 听着, 我知道我们中 只有一个人能得到认可

205
00:13:57,130 --> 00:14:00,430
And I just wanted to wish both of you the best of luck.
而我也想祝福你们所有人好运

206
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:02,590
Are you crossing your fingers?
你绕手指了?

207
00:14:03,870 --> 00:14:09,830
What, this? No. This.. That's just the result of a childhood injury.
什么?这个?不, 这个... 只是童年受伤的结果

208
00:14:10,710 --> 00:14:13,150
I'm cured!
治好了！

209
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:16,610
Good morning, everybody.
大家早上好

210
00:14:16,780 --> 00:14:19,310
If you go ahead and take your seats we can get started.
如果你坐到座位上 我们就可以开始了

211
00:14:19,690 --> 00:14:22,250
Actually, Dr. Hobart, can I have a word with you?
实际上，哈伯特博士 我能和你说句话吗?

212
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:24,290
And you are?
你是...?

213
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,890
- Ross. - I know. I'm kidding.
- 罗斯 - 我知道, 开玩笑的

214
00:14:30,630 --> 00:14:32,860
Listen, I just want to say, last night..
我只想说, 昨晚...

215
00:14:33,030 --> 00:14:35,090
Dinner was a little awkward.
晚餐不太好

216
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:38,430
- I just wanna make sure we're okay. - Oh, yeah. Absolutely.
-我只想知道我们之间没什么问题 -没问题!绝对没有!

217
00:14:38,610 --> 00:14:41,800
- You didn't tell Charlie what I said, did you? - Oh, no. Of course not.
- 你没有告诉查莉我说过什么吧? - 喔, 没有, 当然没有

218
00:14:42,180 --> 00:14:47,240
Well, thank you. I want you to know, I respect your decision not to give her up.
谢谢你, 我想让你知道我尊重你 没有放弃她的决定

219
00:14:47,410 --> 00:14:50,040
It was the biggest mistake I ever made in my whole life.
放弃她, 是我一生中最大的错误

220
00:14:50,220 --> 00:14:53,810
Well, that and tattooing her name on my shoulder..
呃, 除了这件事 还有我很蠢的把她的名字刺在肩膀上...

221
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:57,020
last night stupidly.
昨天晚上犯的蠢..

222
00:14:58,160 --> 00:14:59,150
Seriously?
真的?

223
00:14:59,330 --> 00:15:02,890
My Nobel Prize was not for moving on.
我的诺贝尔奖可不是为了继续谈论..

224
00:15:04,470 --> 00:15:07,160
- So no hard feelings? - None at all. Good luck today.
- 还难过吗？ - 一点也没有, 祝今天好运!

225
00:15:07,330 --> 00:15:09,000
- Thank you. - Okay.
- 谢谢 - 不客气

226
00:15:09,170 --> 00:15:13,940
All right. The selection committee has chosen the three of you as our finalists.
评选委员会选出你们三人于今天作最后评核。

227
00:15:14,110 --> 00:15:19,050
The ultimate decision will be based on the answers you give to the questions I ask.
最终决定会基于你们如何回答我的问题。

228
00:15:19,210 --> 00:15:21,480
We're gonna go ahead and start with Dr. Li.
先从李博士开始吧。

229
00:15:21,650 --> 00:15:25,810
You claim the field is too reliant on the Linnaean taxonomic system.
李博士 你提出学界太依赖林奈分类系统。

230
00:15:25,990 --> 00:15:28,150
How do you propose to correct this problem?
那你打算怎么解决这个问题？

231
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:31,450
Well, I believe that the answers lie in the osteological evidence.
我相信解决办法在化石证据上

232
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:33,490
- I plan to begin there. - Interesting.
-我打算从那里入手 -很有趣

233
00:15:33,930 --> 00:15:35,660
I guess.
是吗？

234
00:15:36,630 --> 00:15:40,570
Dr. Biely, your proposal includes some fieldwork. Where might that take place?
白莉博士，你的方案有一些挖掘工作 你会从哪里入手呢？

235
00:15:40,730 --> 00:15:43,430
Primarily in the Pierre Shale region of South Dakota.
首先是南达科他州的Pierre Shale地区。

236
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:48,040
Certainly. Very well. And Dr. Geller, when is my birthday?
当然，很好。那盖勒博士 你知道我的生日是什么时候吗？

237
00:15:54,350 --> 00:15:56,250
What? I..
什么？我...我...

238
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,410
Care to venture a guess?
不能猜一下吗？

239
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:06,950
- May 12? - That's not even kind of close.
-5月12号？ -还差很远呢！

240
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:10,400
Dr. Li, how many graduate students will you need?
李博士，你需要要多少个学生呢？

241
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:12,500
- Half a dozen. - I see. And Dr. Biely?
- 6个 -明白了，那白莉博士呢？

242
00:16:12,670 --> 00:16:14,960
Three for excavation, and two for analysis.
三个负责开掘，两个负责分析。

243
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:19,200
Certainly. Dr. Geller, which 1965 Shirelles hit..
当然。盖勒博士，1965年沙伦斯乐队

244
00:16:19,370 --> 00:16:22,400
was later covered by a popular British Invasion band?
被哪支英国乐队盖过风头？

245
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:28,570
What? I need six graduate students.
什么...？我需要6个学生。

246
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:32,550
No, I'm sorry. We were looking for "Baby It's You."
不是！对不起 答案是 “Baby It's You”（宝贝，就是你）

247
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,090
"Baby It's You."
宝贝，就是你。

248
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:38,020
What? Wait just a minute.
什么...？等等，等一下。

249
00:16:38,190 --> 00:16:41,360
None of my questions have anything to do with paleontology.
我的问题没有一条是关于古生物学的。

250
00:16:41,530 --> 00:16:44,000
You're right, I apologize. Scratch the last question.
没错，我该道歉。 那最后一条问题

251
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:46,390
Spell "Boscodictiasaur."
拼写单词Boscodictiasaur。

252
00:16:48,670 --> 00:16:52,000
I've never heard of a "Boscodictiasaur."
恩....我没有听过Boscodictiasaur啊。

253
00:16:52,170 --> 00:16:54,500
Yeah, I just made it up. Spell it.
是，我乱编的单词。快拼。

254
00:16:57,340 --> 00:17:00,800
- Okay. B-O.. - No, it starts with a silent M.
-好的。B - O - S ... -不，开头有个不发音的“M”。

255
00:17:00,980 --> 00:17:03,210
Oh, come on!
噢，拜托！

256
00:17:09,560 --> 00:17:13,050
I can't believe Joey. I hate being called a liar.
我不明白乔伊，我讨厌被人称为骗子。

257
00:17:13,230 --> 00:17:14,660
But you are a liar.
但你是个骗子。

258
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,960
What did I just say?
我刚刚怎么说的？

259
00:17:19,330 --> 00:17:20,630
- Are you still here? - Yes.
-你还在啊？ -是的，而且我还有话说

260
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:25,600
And I'm not just hurt, I'm insulted. When I tell somebody I did something..
我不仅仅是受伤害，我感觉被侮辱了一样。 当我说我已经做了某事...

261
00:17:25,770 --> 00:17:29,610
Okay, hold on, let me just stop you right there, okay? First, you lied. Right?
好了好了... 我打断你一下好吗？ 首先，你说谎，对吗？

262
00:17:29,780 --> 00:17:32,340
Then you lied about lying, okay?
然后，你又说谎去圆谎，好吗？

263
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:35,410
Then you lied about lying about lying, okay?
然后，你又再说谎去圆你刚才圆的谎 是不是？

264
00:17:35,580 --> 00:17:40,990
So before you lie about lying about lying about lying about lying..
所以在你说谎去圆你刚才 为圆谎...而说的谎...的那个谎言...

265
00:17:42,990 --> 00:17:44,860
Stop lying.
不要说谎啦！

266
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:47,650
Why are you so sure I didn't watch this tape?
为什么你这么肯定我没有看过那带子？

267
00:17:47,830 --> 00:17:49,920
You wanna know why? You wanna know why?
你想知道...? 你想知道为什么？

268
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:52,360
Well, this is going well.
事情发展得不错呢。

269
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,500
Here's how I know you didn't watch.
这就是我知道你没看的原因了。

270
00:17:55,670 --> 00:18:00,540
If you had seen what was on this tape, believe me, you'd have some comments.
如果你看了这带子，你绝对不会没有话说的。

271
00:18:00,710 --> 00:18:03,510
All right, remember, I got paid a lot of money for this..
听好，我收了很多钱才去拍这个广告

272
00:18:03,680 --> 00:18:05,870
and it only aired in Japan.
而且只在日本地区放映。

273
00:18:06,780 --> 00:18:08,480
Ichiban.
一级棒

274
00:18:09,850 --> 00:18:12,010
Ichiban, lipstick for men.
男用唇膏！

275
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:27,790
Ichiban, lipstick for men.
男用唇膏！

276
00:18:31,540 --> 00:18:33,970
And that's how I know you didn't watch the tape.
这就是我知道你没看的原因！

277
00:18:37,010 --> 00:18:39,410
He really is a chameleon.
他真的是一条变色龙呢。

278
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:50,550
Well, Gladys, say hello to your new home.
格拉达斯，给你的新家打个招呼吧！

279
00:18:53,730 --> 00:18:56,390
- Oh, my. - Wow.
-我的...！ -哇！

280
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:59,790
Oh, she is so nice and big.
噢！她真漂亮，又显眼！

281
00:19:01,670 --> 00:19:07,830
Oh, Monica, where are you going to display Gladys, oh, so proudly?
噢！莫尼卡，你会把她放到什么地方 让格拉达斯显的得体呢？

282
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:13,110
- I haven't really settled on a spot yet. - How about right above the TV?
-我还没决定放在哪里！ -那，不如放在电视机上面吧！

283
00:19:13,310 --> 00:19:17,770
That way, it will be the first thing that you see when you walk in the door.
这样的话，人们一进门就马上看得到了！

284
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:22,450
Yeah, yeah, and you can get rid of that French poster.
好啊，好啊！那你就可以丢掉那法国的海报了。

285
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:24,560
- I like that poster. - Really?
-我喜欢那海报啊！ -是吗？

286
00:19:25,030 --> 00:19:27,190
It doesn't have anything coming out of it.
它没有东西可以“冒”出来啊。

287
00:19:28,230 --> 00:19:30,700
Or maybe there's someplace for her in your bedroom?
又或者你的卧室里有空位吗？

288
00:19:30,860 --> 00:19:34,630
- There's nothing above your bed. - Are you still here?
-噢！你床头还空着呢！ -你还在这里住吗？

289
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:41,470
Stupid Nobel Prize winner.
愚蠢的诺贝尔奖获得者！

290
00:19:47,810 --> 00:19:49,650
Oh, hi. Hello.
噢！嗨！你好！

291
00:19:49,820 --> 00:19:54,250
Have you come to ask me some more paleontology-related questions?
呃，你是来问我古生物学的问题的吗？

292
00:19:54,420 --> 00:19:58,550
Your grandmother's nickname, perhaps? Ann-Margret's pant size?
呃...可能你要问我你祖母的小名吧？ 还是你马格莉特阿姨内裤的尺寸？

293
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:05,590
